manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: A graphic novel for children ages 6 to 9. Marie Curie was the brilliant, trailblazing scientist who discovered radium and coined the term radioactivity. She is the only woman ever awarded two Nobel Prizes--one in physics and one in chemistry. She helped develop the use of X-rays and radiation therapies that have had a lasting impact on medicine and human health. This is her story.

It's Her Story: Rosa Parks: A Graphic Novel Unicorns Have Bad Manners The Sheep Who Wouldn't Sleep - A Story About Self-Soothing and Mindfulness This Book Is Upside Down Beasties Love Booties Nook - A Book About Kindness, Inclusion, Confidence, Trust, and Friendship More Great Children's Books!

Me Readers and First Smart Pads with 8-Book Library With the Me Reader your little one can select which of their 8 included books they want to read, and press the color and shape coded buttons to hear it read out loud. The My First Smart pad is a double sided tablet that allows your little one to go through their included 8-book set and complete over 100 interactive activities. Sound and Song Books Sound and song books offer a hands on interactive experience for young readers. The multi sensory reading adventure stimulates their imagination, while pressing the sound buttons helps with their matching, comparing, and motor skills. My First Library Book Blocks Twelve Just-My-Size tiny board books come packaged in a fantastic case! Your little one will love carrying the case and taking out/putting back their books while developing a love for reading and early motor skills. Look and Find Activity Books Search for hidden objects in wonderfully illustrated scenes! Whether your little one is a Disney Princess or a PAW Patrol pup, PI Kids has the perfect Look and Find for you! Look and Find are available as hardcover books and My First Look and Find are available as board books.

Phoenix International Publications, Inc. At Phoenix International Publications, Inc., we are committed to crafting engaging, educational, and entertaining books for young readers to encourage a lifelong love of story time. Together with licensing partners Disney, Nickelodeon, Sesame Workshop, Eric Carle, among others, and our own collection of family favorite original authors and illustrators, we’ve worked to interlace beloved characters with charming illustrations, activities, sounds, and songs for over three decades. Our stories, and eye for digital advancement, provide a unique interactive reading experience that will delight any child and inspire a lifelong love of reading for the whole family. Our PI Kids brand is also recognized worldwide and our books have been translated into more than 35 languages.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for kiddos curious about Curie.
reviews.reviewText: My daughter wanted to be Curie for her wax museum presentation at school(she's in 3rd grade) so I bought her this book since she didn't know a lot about her. She loved this book and was so excited to add details from it to her speech.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 4, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Story--Not Dry at All
reviews.reviewText: Sometimes biographies for children seem a bit too dry for me, and often times the one about women (to specifically inspire girls) are super cheesy and off-putting. This one, however is a real winner. It's genuinely interesting, the author wasn't overly dramatic to make it unrealistic (to make it even More inspiring) and my son enjoyed it just as much as my daughter. GREAT BOOK.
